# initial_program.py

import random

# EVOLVE-BLOCK-START
def run_search():
    n = 47
    # all grid points
    grid = [(x,y) for x in range(n) for y in range(n)]
    S = []
    random.shuffle(grid)
    for (x,y) in grid:
        ok = True
        # check collinearity against every pair already in S
        slopes = set()
        for x1, y1 in S:
            if x - x1 == 0:
                slope = float('inf')  # Vertical line
            else:
                slope = (y - y1) / (x - x1)
            
            if slope in slopes:
                ok = False
                break
            
            slopes.add(slope)

        if ok:
            S.append((x,y))
    return S
# EVOLVE-BLOCK-END
